Source: user-specific-alternatives
Section: x11
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Cody Garver <cody@elementary.io>
Build-Depends: cmake (>= 2.8),
               debhelper (>= 9),
               libglib2.0-dev,
               libgranite-dev,
               valac
Standards-Version: 3.9.7

Package: user-specific-alternatives
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Make Debian alternatives system honor per-user preferences
 This is a wrapper that allows Debian alternatives system to launch
 the application preferred by a specific user instead of a system-wide and often
 implicit default, e.g. for "x-www-browser" alternative.

Package: user-specific-alternatives-dbg
Architecture: any
Section: debug
Priority: extra
Depends: user-specific-alternatives (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Enhances: user-specific-alternatives
Description: Make Debian alternatives system honor per-user preferences (debugging symbols)
 This is a wrapper that allows Debian alternatives system to launch
 the application preferred by a specific user instead of a system-wide and often
 implicit default, e.g. for "x-www-browser" alternative.
 .
 This package contains debugging symbols for user-specific-alternatives.
